1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 54-06-14.7 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to shared leave for state employees.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 54-06-14.7 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 54-06-14.7. State leave sharing program - Rulemaking. (Retroactive application -
7 See note )
8 1. The human resource management services division of the office of management and
9 budget shall establish a state leave sharing program for permanent employees of the
10 state. The program must provide for a mechanism for state employees to donate
11 accrued annual and sick leave to an employee who does not have available leave who
12 is suffering from a severe, extreme, or life-threatening condition, or who is caring for
13 an immediate relative or household member who is suffering from a severe, extreme,
14 or life-threatening condition.
15 2. A temporary employee or contracted employee with a limited-term appointment is not
16 eligible to participate in the leave sharing program. An employee may not use more
17 than four months donated leave in any twelve-month period and an employee may not
18 retain leave beyond the occurrence necessitating the leave.
19 3. The human resource management services division shall:
20 a. Require medical certification from a physician, physician assistant, psychologist,
21 or advanced practice nurse practitioner verifying the severe, extreme, or
